CommonFields.Title: Core@Double-Shell Structured Nanocomposites: A Route to High Dielectric Constant and Low Loss Material
Author: Huang, Yanhui
Huang, Xingyi
Schadler, Linda S.
He, Jinliang
Jiang, Pingkai
CommonFields.Location: Department of Polymer Science and Engineering, Shanghai Key Laboratory of Electrical Insulation and Thermal Aging, Shanghai Jiao Tong University, Shanghai 200240, China

Mixing.Description: 2 g brominated BaTiO3 nanoparticles (BaTiO3–APS–Br) and 50 ml DMF were combined in a round-bottomed flask and sonicated for 30 min.

Additive.Description: 0.25 g CuBr was added and the flask was sealed with a rubber plug.

ChooseParameter.Other: The oxygen in the flask was carefully removed by evacuating and back-filling with N2 gas three times.

Additive.Description: MMA and 0.3 g PMDETA were added by syringe.
MMA and 0.3 g PMDETA were added by syringe.

ChooseParameter.Other: The products were re-dispersed in acetone, and the mixture was centrifuged; this cycle was repeated four times.

Dielectric_and_Impedance_Spectroscopy_An.Equipment: Novocontrol GmbH Concept 40 broadband dielectric spectrometer
Precision Premier II ferroelectric polarization tester

Thermogravimetric_Analysis.Description: with a heating rate of 20 C/min under a nitrogen flow

temperature.description: unspecified, assumed to be room temperature
